Permissions
Every file/dir has 3 types of permissions â†’ r (read), w (write), x (execute).
They apply to 3 groups â†’ u (owner), g (group), o (others).
r = read (4)
w = write (2)
x = execute (1)
-rw-r--r--  1 ubuntu ubuntu  20 Sep 15 23:10 file1.txt
-
rw- â†’ owner can read/write
r-- â†’ group can only read
r-- â†’ others can only read
Chmod 755 meaning
Owner: rwx
Group: r-x
Others: r-x
